<subSubSection id="C35552F7FF95BF3DA599485C42E51EAC" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF0017CFF95BF3DA599485C42E51EAC" blockId="1.[151,1437,295,465]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF95BF3DA599485C43581EF4" bold="true" box="[199,324,367,393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Comment.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4F7AFFFF95BF3DA413484343CF1EF4" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2012" box="[333,467,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ablectum">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF95BF3DA413484343CF1EF4" box="[333,467,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">L. ablectum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recognized in same locality of Houhe Natural Reserve, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE7C8DFF95BF3DA1EA485C47791EF4" author="Li, W. - R. &amp; Dai, C. - C. &amp; Li, L. - Z." box="[1204,1381,367,393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" pagination="47 - 53" refId="ref3725" refString="Li, W. - R., Dai, C. - C. &amp; Li, L. - Z. (2013) A new species and additional records of Lobrathium Mulsant &amp; Rey (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae) from China. ZooKeys, 326, 47 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 326.5970" type="journal article" year="2013">
Li 
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF95BF3DA18B484347131EF4" box="[1237,1295,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
. The known distribution is confined to the Daba Shan (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE7C8DFF95BF3DA7BD48A041641ED0" author="Assing, V." box="[739,888,403,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref3564" refString="Assing, V. (2012) A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 61, 49 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 61.2.413 - 453" type="journal article" year="2012">Assing 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and the Wuling Shan in 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF95BF3DA1F548A046EE1ED0" box="[1195,1266,403,429]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Hubei</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF95BF3DA05F48A047781ED0" box="[1281,1380,403,429]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF95BF3DA5C9488442E91EAC" box="[151,245,439,465]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
